    dc:title "A revision of the treehopper genus Bubalopa Stål illuminates the systematics of Hyphinoini (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Membracidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577281>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577293>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577277>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577283> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577281>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Hyphinoe obliqua (Walker, 1858). Adult: A) Frontal view, B) lateral view, C) dorsal view. Last instar exuvia: D) dorsal view, E) frontal view, F) lateral view, G) close-up frontal view, H) frontolateral view. as: abdominal scoli; hs: head scoli; mss: mesothoracic scoli; mts: metathoracic scoli; pms: premetopidium scoli; pos: postmetopidium scoli." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5577281/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577293>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Bubalopa furcata (Fairmaire, 1846). A) male abdomen, oval pits indicated by a rectangle. B) Female, ventral view. Fourth-fifth instar nymph: C) Frontal view. D) Head, anteroventral view. E) Head, ventral view. F) Lateral view, left side. F) Lateral view, right side. G) Frontolateral view. H) Dorsal view. ach: lateral abdominal chalazae; as: abdominal scoli; hs: head scoli; mss: mesothoracic scoli; mts: metathoracic scoli; pms: premetopidium scoli; pos: postmetopidium scoli; shb: suprahumeral horns bud; sps: small spinelike scoli." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5577293/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577277>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Live specimens of Hyphinoe obliqua (Walker, 1858). Nymphs: A) and B) 1/3rd instar, C) 4/5th instar, D) Last instar exuvia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5577277/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577283>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Live specimens of Bubalopa furcata. Nymphs: A) habitus of an early instar. B–D). Fourth/fifth instar nymph: B) habitus in lateral view, C) 4/5th instar nymph resting near the stipule of its host plant (Senna pistaciifolia), D) habitus in lateral view. Adult: E) frontal habitus, F) lateral habitus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5577283/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

